6 An Act relating to wildlife; authorizing the
Department of Wildlife Conservation to implement a
7 system for registration and licensing of hunting
guides; excluding certain entities; providing for
8 promulgation of rules; providing for codification;
and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4-112B of Title 29, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. The Department of Wildlife Conservation shall, for the
16 safety and security of landowners and hunters in this state, create
17 a system of registration and licensing for any person or entity
18 providing guiding services in this state, excluding those services
19 provided for commercial hunting facilities and landowners providing
20 guiding services on their own property.
21 B. The Department shall promulgate all rules necessary to
22 implement the provisions of this section.
23 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
